  <TEXT> 
	 <BODY> 
		<DIV1 TYPE="letter"><PB N="[1]"> 
		  <OPENER> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE> 
				  <DATE VALUE="1813-09-06"><ABBR EXPAN="September">Sept</ABBR> 6th
					 1813</DATE> </ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS> 
			 <SALUTE>Sir</SALUTE></OPENER> 
		  <P>From recent orders 
			 <ABBR EXPAN="received">recd</ABBR> from 
			 <ABBR EXPAN="Governor">Gov</ABBR> 
			 <NAME TYPE="person"> Blount</NAME> and from an apprehension that an
			 attack is meditated by the 
			 <NAME TYPE="person">Creek</NAME> Indians on some part of the frontier
			 of 
			 <NAME TYPE="place">Tennessee</NAME> it becomes my duty to order that
			 defensive measures be <ORIG REG="immediately">immediatly</ORIG> adopted to
			 secure and protect the frontier of my division you will therefore without delay
			 put the first Brigade of militia in the best possible state of defence by
			 notifying them of the meditated attack by the Creek Indians and requiring them
			 to be ready to act at a moments warning to repel any invasions that may be made
			 or structured on any part of the Brigade now under your Command &amp; treat the
			 invaders or enemies to our peace and in the event of an attack made or of your
			 knowledge of the approach <PB N="[2]"> of the enemy to the frontiers you will
			 Instantly order a Competent force not only to repel them but to Chastise and as
			 far as in your power utterly <ORIG REG="destroy">distroy</ORIG> them &amp;
			 <ORIG REG="pursue">persue</ORIG> as far as prudence will dictate you will
			 without delay Communicate to me all the information you Can <ORIG
			 REG="acquire">accquire</ORIG> relation to movements &amp; disposition of the
			 enemy together with such orders as you may from time to time Issue with an
			 account of all necessary expenditures for supplies 
			 <ABBR EXPAN="et cetera">&amp;c</ABBR> you will be Careful not to
			 molest any friendly Indian but treat them with <ORIG
			 REG="hospitality">hospitiallity</ORIG> &amp; friendship so long as their
			 Conduct is proper</P> 
		  <CLOSER> 
			 <SALUTE>I am respectfully</SALUTE> 
			 <SALUTE>your 
				<ABBR EXPAN="obedient servant">obt sert</ABBR></SALUTE> 
			 <SIGNED> 
				<NAME TYPE="person">John Cocke</NAME></SIGNED> <ADD>orders similar
			 to the above 
			 <ABBR EXPAN="Issued">Isd</ABBR> to 
			 <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="General">Genl</ABBR> Taylor</NAME>
			 but finding he is <ORIG REG="absent">absan<ADD
			 PLACE="supralinear">t</ADD></ORIG> I send them to your new Command my <LB> 
			 <ABBR EXPAN="John Cocke">J C</ABBR></ADD></CLOSER> 
		</DIV1> 
	 </BODY> 
